  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Creature Type.</strong> You are a Humanoid.<br /><br /><strong>Size.</strong> You are Medium.<br /><br /><strong>Speed.</strong> Your Speed is 30 feet.<br /><br /><strong>Darkvision.</strong> You have Darkvision to a range of 60 feet.<br /><br /><strong>Beasthide Shifting.</strong> As a Bonus Action, you can assume a more bestial appearance. This transformation lasts for 1 minute, until you die, or until you revert to your normal appearance as a Bonus Action. When you shift, you gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li>Temporary Hit Points equal to 2 times your Proficiency Bonus.</li><li>You can roll 1 Hit Die and gain additional Temporary Hit Points equal to the result. While shifted, you have a +1 bonus to your Armor Class.</li></ul><p>You can shift a number of times equal to your Proficiency Bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest.</p><p>When you reach character level 5, if you are reduced to 0 hit points but not killed outright while shifted, you can drop to 1 hit point instead. Your transformation immediately ends as a result. Once you use this trait, you cannot do so again until you finish a Long Rest.<br /><br /><strong>Bestial Instincts.</strong> Channeling the beast within, you have proficiency in one of the following skills of your choice: Acrobatics, Athletics, Intimidation, or Survival.<br /><br /><strong>Feral Impulses.</strong> You have Advantage on saving throws you make to avoid or end the &amp;Reference[Blinded apply=false], &amp;Reference[Deafened apply=false], and &amp;Reference[Weakened apply=false] condition on yourself.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
